transcript: My advisor is like "But you don't actually make your clothes," and I'm like "Well, I made this coat that I'm wearing. And I made my purse,"  and he's like "Ok, but you didn't make the fabric, right?" Which the answer was no, I hadn't made that fabric. So for my prospectus defense, I spun yarn that I then knit into a sweater vest that I wore to my defense so that I could specifically say that I was wearing clothing that I did spin myself.
title: Morgan
